article.description: Kelli Roehrig matched her season-high with 23 points, leading four Spartans in double figures as No. 11 Michigan State beat Vermont 85-57.
article.headline: Spartans get sixth straight win
article.linkText: Roehrig sparks Michigan State rout of Vermont
article.story:
EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Kelli Roehrig matched her season-high with 23 points, leading four Spartans in double figures as No. 11 Michigan State beat Vermont 85-57 on Tuesday night.

Lindsay Bowen had 15 points, Liz Shimek 14 and Kristin Haynie 13 to go with eight rebounds, nine assists and four steals in the sixth straight win for the Spartans (10-1). They played as part of a rare doubleheader with the Michigan State men hosting UCLA.

The Catamounts (3-4) were led by Lani Boardman with 16 points and Katie McNamara with 14 but were outshot 50 percent to 32.8 percent. That included 8-of-12 from the field and 7-of-8 from the foul line for Roehrig.

Michigan State, which will play at No. 8 Connecticut on Dec. 29, sprinted to a 16-6 lead and held a 43-30 halftime advantage. Roehrig had 15 points at the break, while Haynie and Bowen added nine apiece.

The Catamounts shot their first free throw with 15:37 to play and fell behind by 33 points midway through the second half. The Spartans finished with edges of 47-31 in rebounds and 22-12 in assists.

Michigan State trailed just once, 2-0, in its fifth straight home win this season.
